# @rbxts/testez
## Information
This package wraps Roblox's [TestEZ](https://github.com/Roblox/testez) tool with TypeScript typings.

[Click here to read the official documentation for TestEZ.](https://roblox.github.io/testez/) This wrapper simply wraps all of the TestEZ API in TypeScript type files.

## Usage
To use the TestEZ globals in a file, add the following line to the top of the file:

```ts
/// <reference types="@rbxts/testez/globals" />
```

Then run using a script much like the following:

```ts
import { ReplicatedStorage } from "@rbxts/services";
import TestEZ from "@rbxts/testez";

const results = TestEZ.TestBootstrap.run([ ReplicatedStorage.TS.tests ]);

if (results.errors.size() > 0 || results.failureCount > 0) {
    error("Tests Failed!!");
}
```
